column5: Saw a few huts out there yesterday near the shore. No idea how thick the ice is so beware.

There was 4 to 6" last weekend when I was there straight out in the middle of the lake.  A guy from the park was running around taking measurement of the ice, preparing to drag huts out.  He was going to hold off a few days based on his measurements at that time.  There must be a few more inches now, if he's dragging huts out already.  Just a guess though.  Guys running snowmobiles all over the lake last weekend.
Nick, I just dropped you a PM, you gotta clean out your Inbox!
Wow.  First time I've ever deleted a message before.  Since I started in 2009.  Fire a way bill!
